{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1772117591,"nonce":"C1pkjYvkm0azM+HuBcz1bjRFg/M=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87uLmL_zwAAAAVhPsF0"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772118743,"nonce":"YN3edHK4WEQx7v0KY7oI6cXIvf0=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87sd4Lo","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/272#issuecomment-3967255272"},"message":"## Triage Report\n\n### Scope Assessment\n\n**Well-scoped?** Partially. The deliverable is clear (one file), but the content scope is ambitious. A per-principle checklist × 10 principles + per-ADR mapping × 6 ADRs + transparency checklist + consequences table + layering rules is a lot of material. Risk of producing something so long it violates the \"Only what's needed\" principle it's supposed to enforce.\n\n### Principle Alignment\n\n| Principle | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Only what's needed | **Watch** | Could easily become bloated. Should it start minimal and grow based on what skills actually reference? |\n| A change includes its consequences | **Action needed** | Issue doesn't mention updating `.agent/knowledge/README.md` to index the new file |\n| Capture decisions | OK | The guide itself captures evaluation rationale |\n| Workspace vs. project separation | OK | Layering rules section addresses this directly |\n\n### ADR Relevance\n\n- **ADR-0003** (project-agnostic): Checklists should not embed project-specific assumptions\n- **ADR-0006** (shared instruction file): Guide will be referenced by Claude skills but should be framework-agnostic markdown — consistent with ADR-0006's pattern\n\n### Concerns\n\n1. **Size risk**: 5 major sections. If each principle gets a detailed checklist, this file could hit 300+ lines — defeating context-efficient evaluation. Consider a concise lookup table rather than prose.\n2. **Missing consequence**: `.agent/knowledge/README.md` index needs updating.\n3. **Dependency on #271**: Guide should reference \"Only what's needed\" not \"Radical simplicity\" — #271 is now merged.\n4. **Validation**: Acceptance criteria say \"covers all 10 principles\" but not \"verified against actual codebase behavior.\" Consider testing checklists against a real PR.\n\n### Recommendations\n\n- Add acceptance criterion: update `.agent/knowledge/README.md`\n- Consider a format constraint (e.g., under 200 lines) to keep it context-efficient\n- Consider starting minimal and letting later skills drive what detail is needed\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772125137,"nonce":"BlMJ2IaptBg9LXQEyv1rUOG9bjw=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87uLmL_zwAAAAVhfGua"},"status":2}]}